main event: On September 7, 1964, a bright blue light was observed approximately 20 feet off the ground near Whiteman Air Force Base in Missouri.
interesting points: The object was reported to be a blue light observed south of several missile sites., The sighting lasted for about one hour., The sighting was categorized as visual/visual, indicating no physical evidence was collected., There were no photographs or other forms of evidence included with the report., The data collected was deemed insufficient for further evaluation.
witness description: USAF Security personnel reported the observation.
